stylometry: The trade off relationship between price and demand a company must consider when setting a price for a product or service is important for any company.  They have to decide whether or not how high or low the price is going to be in relation to the quality of service you receive.  For instance if a company is going to raise a premium price for a product the company is planning on using the best service available for the customer.  If customers complain about the price and management feels they need to make a change and lower the price, management will have to make a decision of the level of quality the product will have if they lower the price.  The management question is do they think lowering the price and quality of service will result in greater profit and revenue than the current price associated with the quality of service.  You would develop a model about this with different price ranges and level of quality as the constraints.  They key in the proble would be the amount of people who buy the product.  You would have to use a forecast or a break even analysis to see where you would break even.  You could also use the response you have received so far in selling the product.
